This paper proposes a solution to the mode collapse problem in GANs, which is a common issue in the field of machine learning and specifically in the subfield of generative models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the proposed solution involves using multiple discriminators, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of a diversity parameter, which is a concept that is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and graph theory (cs.GR).
